<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 24 at 3:21AM CDT until May 24 at 4:00AM CDT by NWS Lubbock</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 345 AM CDT
FOR CHILDRESS...NORTH CENTRAL COTTLE AND EAST CENTRAL HALL
COUNTIES...
At 321 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles northwest of
Childress, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Childress, Tell, Kirkland and Estelline.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
